Welcome to my second channel dedicated to easier drawing tutorials for younger artists. My lessons teaches art for kids through step by step on original and fun characters. To access my flagship channel Cartooning 4 Kids please visit me at https://www.youtube.com/cartooning4kids. I have thousands of step by step lessons available. Or you can stay with me right here. :)

I heard my fans loud and clear so I'm responding with more entry level lessons. All my lessons are original artwork. I believe art is the foundation for many things in life. Please visit my website for more information at http://www.cartooning4kids.com. I'll continue to add more features and content to my services. Thanks for watching.

Looking for fun and easy ways to improve your drawing skills? You've come to the right place. Art is an essential life skill that everyone should learn. My channel is dedicated to teaching anyone how to draw using simple step by step techniques that work. I started this channel during the height of my career as an art director working in the video game industry. I have 2 young children that love to draw but my busy work schedule prevented me from teaching them myself. So, I started drawing and uploading videos every day from the back seat of my car. WELCOME! So pleased to have you here!

Dear Parent & Teachers,
Easy to follow crafts and ideas for all age groups from RedTedArt.com. The crafts are designed to be made from every day items, so you can usually get crafting straight away! I have a number of playlists to help you find your way

Teens & Tweens - are basically the sort of crafts that I used to LOVE to make make when I was a teenager.  Often a little more skilled, but no reason why younger kids can't have a go with the help of a parent.
Kids Crafts - the sort of crafts my kids currently enjoy, usually involves lots of recycling or basic craft items such as paper!
Seasonal Playlist - I have also created seasonal playlists and swap these around according  to the time of year.

These videos are designed for "Together Projects" when working with younger kids. Teenages, should be able to complete them by themselves.

ENJOY! FEEDBACK ALWAYS WELCOMED!
